  "timeframe": "15m",
  "market_context": "NQ 15-minute chart on Thu 13 Feb '25. Price formed a consolidation around 22,560–22,580 then swept the consolidation low into the 22,420–22,460 area, setting up a bullish bias scenario with points of interest above and previous highs as draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "Although bias was bullish after the sweep, neither a candle two closure nor a candle three closure formed to validate the reversal, meaning the fractal model criteria were not met despite price ultimately trading higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the consolidation range and noted that price swept out the low of the consolidation, establishing a bullish bias.",
    "Checked for a candle two closure at the sweep — confirmed it did not form.",
    "Looked for a candle three closure as the next validation — confirmed it also did not form.",
    "Concluded that while higher prices could be anticipated, the model criteria did not align, so no entry was warranted.",
    "Explained the valid alternative: wait for a closure through the series of down-close candles to form a new protected swing with points of interest before trading higher into previous highs.",
    "Noted that in this specific case no new swing formed to trigger the model."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Do not pattern-trade the model or randomly choose swing points. Candle two and candle three closures must work together with points of interest and context to confirm a valid entry — anticipation alone is not a setup.",
